<br>
The root of the matter all comes down to life at conception.  My opinion is that two gametes come together and at that moment human life exists.  That life is a parasite that attaches itself to a host, or mother, and then proceeds to feed off that host and grow.<br>
<br>
That life has its own DNA which means it is not part of the mother.  Again, it is a parasite.  It will remain a parasite until it is 18 years old and you boot it out the door.    The question you must ask yourself is what value do you place on it?  At what stage in its development does it have enough value to be given the right to life?  If we can kill it in the 3rd trimester for whatever reason, then can’t we use those same reasons to kill it when it is 4 years old?<br>
<br>
I don’t believe that one’s development should dictate one’s worth.  Each year, I don’t become more of a human.  I’ve always been human.  I’m no more human now than I was 10 years ago.  So I don’t believe that being located outside the mother means that you are more human or have more value than being located inside the mother.  I believe it is equally wrong to kill a fetus, child, or an adult.<br>
<br>
Now of course there are always exceptions.  I believe it is ok to kill someone in self defense for example.  Likewise, there should be exceptions made based on the circumstances involving unwanted pregnancy.  I’ll discuss two exceptions, but there are probably be more out there.<br>
<br>
I have no problem if a mother decides to abort a fetus if it places her life in danger.  You can not ask someone to sacrifice one’s self in order to save another life that may end in vain.<br>
<br>
The 2nd exception is when a life is created from the act of rape.  We already have one victim.  Not only does she have to deal with the trauma of the rape, she has to make a choice about the life growing inside of her.  I can understand if everything is just too much for her and she decides to abort the fetus.  But keep in mind that there is already one victim, does there need to be two?  I hope that the mom would be strong enough to try to prevent a 2nd victim, but I can understand if she chooses not to.<br>
<br>
Anyway, that is my opinion.<br>
